Deputy President William Ruto on Thursday led the Kenya Kwanza Alliance rally in Nyamira county as the race to presidency continues. Ruto was accompanied by his counterparts ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi and Ford Kenya leader Moses Wetangula in a hunt for votes. Kenya Kwanza visited North Mugirango, West Mugirango and Kitutu Masaba and shared their vision for the country with the people of Ekerubo Gietai, Mabundu and Gesima Market. Ruto also presented a bus to Nyameru High School. The trio was accompanied by MPs Shadrack Mose (Kitutu Masaba), Vincent Kemosi (West Mugirango), Silvanus Osoro (South Mugirango), Joash Nyamoko (North Mugirango), Ezekiel Machogu (Nyaribari Masaba). Others are Millicent Omanga (Nominated), Kimani Ichung'wah (Kikuyu), Majimbo Kalasinga (Kabuchai), Njuguna Wanjiku (Kiambaa) and Walter Nyambati (former Kitutu Masaba MP). Ruto said that Kenya Kwanza is keen on addressing the needs of every Kenyan irrespective of their background in the society, adding "United we will transform our country."